<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - FUEL SYSTEM - Fuel Filter and
        Piping - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <figure id="f1201210" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3294.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Fuel Filter Tower</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter and Support Bracket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Stud Nuts (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the fuel filter tower to the cylinder head. Install the four stud nuts and tighten
                them to the standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201209" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3293.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing Hoses to Regulating Valve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Pressure Regulating Valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Hoses</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new O-rings and seals onto the fuel pressure regulating valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the regulating valve to the fuel filter with two mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts to
                the standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>On earlier model engines with non-split shot fuel systems, the two fuel hoses are for fuel return
                    from the cylinder heads. On later model engines with split shot fuel systems, the two fuel hoses are
                    for fuel supply from the pump to the regulating valve.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the fuel hoses to the fuel pressure regulating valve. Tighten the hose fittings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201211" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3282.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Attaching the Fuel Tubes</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter Lid</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Supply to Fuel Transfer Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Tandem Lift Pump to Fuel Filter</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Filter to Fuel Transfer Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Tie Strap or Retaining Clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Drain</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the three fuel tubes between the fuel transfer pump and the fuel filter.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a tie strap or retaining clip to attach the three fuel tubes together.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the fuel filter drain line. Secure it to the fuel filter with hose clamps.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
